The paper focuses on using deep reinforcement learning for dexterous manipulation, which is a problem commonly studied in robotics (cs.RO). The use of concept networks to decompose problems and incorporate prior knowledge is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques to perceive the objects being manipulated (cs.CV). Finally, the use of a Kinova JACO arm and MuJoCo simulation involves control systems and robotics (cs.SY).
